The ANC has allegedly given instruction for all DA-initiated projects in the City of Johannesburg Metro to be canned even if they were effective, and the governing party was forging ahead with purging all senior officials who worked under ousted the DA-led administration, the DA says. DA caucus leader in the City of Johannesburg Funzela Ngobeni said he received complaints that political instructions had been given to the Johannesburg Metropolitan Police Department that any project that was initiated and associated with the DA must be canned. This was regardless of how effective it was. Former DA member of the mayoral...